Introducao

Meu objetivo aqui √© disponibilizar o c√≥digo de algumas an√°lises para os dados de COVID-19 por estado coletado pelo Wesley Cota (UFV).

Lendo os dados

Os dados s√£o lidos diretamente do github do Wesley Cota que agrega dados em n√≠vel municipal do minist√©rio da sa√∫de e das secretarias de sa√∫de estaduais.

d.estados <- 
  read.csv("https://raw.githubusercontent.com/wcota/covid19br/master/cases-brazil-states.csv",
           sep=",", encoding = "UTF-8", stringsAsFactors = F)

Plots

tbl.covid.state <- d.estados %>% 
  filter(state != "TOTAL" & totalCases >= 100) %>% 
  mutate(
    date = ymd(date)
  )
tbl.covid.state %>%  
  ggplot(aes( y = totalCases, x = date, group = state, color = state)) + 
  geom_point(show.legend = F) +
  geom_line(show.legend = F) + 
  geom_label( data = tbl.covid.state %>% 
                filter(date == max(tbl.covid.state$date)), 
              mapping = aes(x = date, y = totalCases, label = state ), 
              show.legend = F ) +
  scale_y_continuous(trans = "log10") +
  ylab("Total de casos de COVID-19") +
  xlab("Dia") +
  theme_bw(base_size = 14) + 
  ggtitle("Estados com mais de 100 casos reportados")

tbl.covid.state %>%  
  #filter(deaths > 1) %>% 
  ggplot(aes( y = deaths, x = date, group = state, color = state)) + 
  geom_point(show.legend = F) +
  geom_line(show.legend = F) + 
  geom_label( data = tbl.covid.state %>% 
                filter(date == max(date) & deaths > 1), 
              mapping = aes(x = date, y = deaths, label = state ), 
              show.legend = F ) +
  #scale_y_continuous(trans = "log10") +
  ylab("√ìbitos por COVID-19") +
  xlab("Dia") +
  theme_bw(base_size = 14) + 
  ggtitle("Estados com algum √≥bito")

tbl.covid.state %>% 
  ggplot(aes( y = newCases, x = totalCases, group = state, color = state)) + 
  geom_line( alpha = 0.5, show.legend = F) +
  geom_label( data = tbl.covid.state %>% 
              filter(date == max(tbl.covid.state$date)), 
              mapping = aes(y = newCases, x = totalCases, label = state ), 
              show.legend = F ) +
  scale_x_continuous(trans = "log10") +
  scale_y_continuous(trans = "log10") +
  xlab("Total de casos") +
  ylab("Casos novos") +
  theme_bw(base_size = 14)
